        <div class="box"></div>


        <section class="theme">
          <h1 class="main-title">REST</h1>

          <nav class="main-nav">
            <h4>Shortcut</h4>
            <ul>
              <li><a href="#re_s">Sleep</a></li>
              <li><a href="#re_b-t">Break Time</a></li>
              <li><a href="#re_c-n-s">Central Nervous System Fatigue</a></li>
              <li><a href="#re_m">Massage</a></li>
              <li><a href="#re_c">Cardio</a></li>
            </ul>
          </nav>
        </section>


        <section class="rest">
          <div id="re_s">
            <div class="main-wt">
              <h4 class="main-wt-title">Sleep</h4>
              <ul>
                <li>Sleep is very important for the recovery of damaged muscles and the secretion of growth hormone</li>
                <li>Sleep for muscles is recommended at least 7-8 hours</li>
                <li>
                  <span class="cursor" data-modal-target2="#modal172-211">Slow wave sleep(non-REM sleep)</span>
                  <div class="modal2" id="modal172-211">
                    <div class="modal-header">
                      <button data-close-button2 class="close-button">&times;</button>
                    </div>
                    <div class="modal-body">
                      <div class="modal-p">
                        <p>This is the period when growth hormone is most secreted</p>
                        <br>
                        <h5>How to increase slow wave sleep</h5>
                        <p>Pink noise</p>
                        <p>Warm shower</p>
                        <p>Caffeine X</p>
                        <p>Naps longer than 30 minutes X</p>
                        <p>
                          <img src="https://t1.daumcdn.net/cfile/tistory/991C61505A2F4C3C2F" alt="slow wave sleep">
                        </p>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                  <div id="overlay"></div>
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>


          <div id="re_b-t">
            <div class="main-wt">
              <h4 class="main-wt-title">Break Time</h4>
              <ul>
                <li>Multi-joint workouts - long rest periods allow for higher power output. When performing compound
                  multi-joint exercises with heavy weight, it can be effective to take a break of 3 to 5 minutes</li>
                <li>Single-joint exercises - 1-3 minutes will be effective depending on muscle size</li>
                <li>
                  <span class="cursor" data-modal-target2="#modal173-211">Absolute break time?</span>
                  <div class="modal2" id="modal173-211">
                    <div class="modal-header">
                      <button data-close-button2 class="close-button">&times;</button>
                    </div>
                    <div class="modal-body">
                      <div class="modal-p">
                        <p>Short rest time can reduce the output value that can be produced and reduce the exercise
                          volume, which in turn can reduce muscle growth</p>
                        <p>There is no absolute rest time <br> After setting a rough frame, it seems appropriate to take
                          enough rest time to allow one's own breathing to return and properly perform the next set</p>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                  <div id="overlay"></div>
                </li>
                <li>It is recommended that you do not use your cell phone during breaks and take time to give feedback
                  on the exercise you just did</li>
                <li>It is recommended to set the weight for the next set immediately after the main set</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>


          <div id="re_c-n-s">
            <div class="main-wt">
              <h4 class="main-wt-title">Centeral Nervous System Fatigue
              </h4>
              <ul>
                <li>The central nervous system governs the activation of muscle fibers. The central nervous system must
                  fully recover to achieve maximum output</li>
                <li>How to confirm recovery of the central nervous system - If the grip strength is less than 10% than
                  usual, the recovery is less than normal</li>
                <li>
                  Exercises that increase central nervous system fatigue include aerobic exercise(long exercise),
                  multi-joint exercise, large muscle exercise, and short rest
                  <br>
                  [Multi-joint + long rest], [Small muscle + short rest], and [Multi-joint exercise + long time
                  performance X] are recommended for effective exercise
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>


          <div id="re_m">
            <div class="main-wt">
              <h4 class="main-wt-title">Massage</h4>
              <ul>
                <li>
                  <span class="cursor" data-modal-target2="#modal175-211">
                    On a rest day, if you massage the area you exercised the day before with a foam roller or massage
                    ball, it will help you recover will be effective</span>
                  <div class="modal2" id="modal175-211">
                    <div class="modal-header">
                      <button data-close-button2 class="close-button">&times;</button>
                    </div>
                    <div class="modal-body">
                      <div class="modal-p">
                        <p>Through strength training, it is microscopically torn and fatigue substances(lactic acid)
                          accumulate in the fascia surrounding the muscles. At this time, if the fascia is relaxed with
                          a foam roller or massage ball, muscle pain is reduced and the damaged area is healed
                          recover</p>
                        <p>This is because massage promotes blood circulation in the affected area and quickly removes
                          fatigue substances</p>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                  <div id="overlay"></div>
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>


          <div id="re_c">
            <div class="main-wt no-border">
              <h4 class="main-wt-title">CARDIO</h4>
              <ul>
                <li>Stimulates blood circulation to improve physical condition and removes fatigue substances in muscles
                  to quickly heal muscle pain</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>


        <button class="material-symbols-outlined up-arrow"><a href="#upEn">arrow_upward</a></button>

      </div>
